cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.WEB, cs.DS, cs.DB

This paper is primarily focused on a protocol for synchronizing collections of changing Web resources, which is relevant to the fields of digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), and web technologies (cs.WEB). Additionally, the use of XML Sitemaps as a basis for the protocol suggests a potential connection to data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB).
